{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846612992,"sessionID":"ses_2874b5d29ffeeDhVXE2ZEQcEQq","part":{"id":"prt_d78b4d529001UcZbxFYFXqBcwt","messageID":"msg_d78b4bd2d001oMDZOMVY2hys37","sessionID":"ses_2874b5d29ffeeDhVXE2ZEQcEQq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3dbef2d25d3f4ebaa151ee47","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 ŌĆö K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ© Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-007 ŌĆö K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ© |\n8: | Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | L |\n11: | Stage | ST-3 completed |\n12: \n13: ## Atomic Tasks\n14: \n15: ### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n16: \n17: - [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Reconciler` interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n18:   - Methods: `Run(ctx context.Context)`, `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)`\n19:   - Document each method purpose\n20: \n21: - [ ] **TASK-002**: Define `Request` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n22:   - Fields: `Namespace` (string), `Name` (string)\n23:   - Document usage in reconciliation loop\n24: \n25: - [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `Result` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n26:   - Fields: `Requeue` (bool), `RequeueAfter` (time.Duration)\n27:   - Document requeue behavior and priorities\n28: \n29: - [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `ReconcilerConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n30:   - Fields: `ResyncPeriod`, `MaxRetries`, `RateLimitQPS`, `RateLimitBurst`, `ConcurrentReconciles`, `EnableLeaderElection`, `LeaderElectionNamespace`, `LeaderElectionName`\n31:   - All fields documented with comments\n32: \n33: - [ ] **TASK-005**: Implement `DefaultReconcilerConfig()` function\n34:   - Returns default configuration per design spec\n35:   - Defaults: ResyncPeriod=10m, MaxRetries=5, RateLimitQPS=10, RateLimitBurst=20, ConcurrentReconciles=2\n36: \n37: - [ ] **TASK-006**: Define error constants in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n38:   - Constants: `ErrReconcileFailed`, `ErrPodCreationFailed`, `ErrPodUpdateFailed`, `ErrStatusUpdateFailed`, `ErrOwnerRefFailed`, `ErrCacheMiss`, `ErrInvalidSpec`\n39: \n40: - [ ] **TASK-007**: Define `ReconcileError` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go`\n41:   - Fields: `Type` (string), `Message` (string), `Err` (error), `Retryable` (bool)\n42:   - Methods: `Error()`, `Unwrap()`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **TASK-008**: Implement `IsRetryableError()` function\n45:   - Checks `*ReconcileError.Retryable`\n46:   - Checks k8s transient errors: `IsTimeout`, `IsTooManyRequests`, `IsServerTimeout`\n47: \n48: ### Phase 2: ControllerManager Infrastructure\n49: \n50: - [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `ControllerManager` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n51:   - Fields: `config`, `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `informerFactory`, `reconcilers`, `ctx`, `cancel`\n52:   - Informer fields: `agentRuntimeInformer`, `codeInterpreterInformer`, `podInformer`\n53:   - Lister fields: `agentRuntimeLister`, `codeInterpreterLister`, `podLister`\n54:   - Event recorder: `recorder`\n55: \n56: - [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewControllerManager()` constructor\n57:   - Creates versioned clientset and kubernetes clientset\n58:   - Initializes SharedInformerFactory with 10m resync\n59:   - Returns initialized *ControllerManager or error\n60: \n61: - [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `AddReconciler()` method\n62:   - Appends reconciler to manager's reconcilers slice\n63: \n64: - [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `SetupInformers()` method\n65:   - Gets typed informers from factory\n66:   - Returns error if setup fails\n67: \n68: - [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `StartInformers()` method\n69:   - Starts informer factory\n70:   - Waits for cache sync with timeout\n71:   - Verifies critical informers synced (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Pod)\n72:   - Gets listers from informers\n73: \n74: - [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `Start()` method\n75:   - Starts informers\n76:   - Waits for cache sync\n77:   - Starts all reconcilers as goroutines\n78:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n79:   - Handles graceful shutdown (workqueue drain)\n80: \n81: - [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement graceful shutdown in `Start()`\n82:   - Shuts down workqueues\n83:   - Waits for workqueue.Done()\n84:   - Logs shutdown progress\n85: \n86: ### Phase 3: AgentRuntimeReconciler\n87: \n88: - [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `AgentRuntimeReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go`\n89:   - Fields: `clientset`, `k8sClient`, `lister`, `podLister`, `recorder`, `workqueue`, `metrics`\n90: \n91: - [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `NewAgentRuntimeReconciler()` constructor\n92:   - Creates reconciler with rate-limiting workqueue\n93:   - Registers event handlers on AgentRuntime informer\n94:   - Registers event handlers on Pod informer (for owned pods)\n95:   - Returns initialized *AgentRuntimeReconciler\n96: \n97: - [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `Run()` method for AgentRuntimeReconciler\n98:   - Creates context from stopCh\n99:   - Starts reconciliation workers (ConcurrentReconciles workers)\n100:   - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n101: \n102: - [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n103:   - Fetches AgentRuntime from lister\n104:   - Handles NotFound (skip reconciliation)\n105:   - Handles deletion (calls `reconcileDeletion()`)\n106:   - Reconciles sandbox pod (calls `reconcileSandboxPod()`)\n107:   - Updates status (calls `updateStatus()`)\n108:   - Records events and metrics\n109:   - Returns Result with requeue logic\n110: \n111: - [ ] **TASK-024**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method\n112:   - Handles finalizer cleanup\n113:   - Deletes owned sandbox pod\n114:   - Removes finalizer\n115:   - Returns Result\n116: \n117: - [ ] **TASK-025**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method\n118:   - Checks if pod exists (from lister cache)\n119:   - If not found: builds and creates new pod\n120:   - If exists: checks if update needed\n121:   - If needs update: delete-and-recreate\n122:   - Returns pod or error\n123: \n124: - [ ] **TASK-026**: Implement event handler methods\n125:   - `enqueueObject(obj interface{})` - casts to AgentRuntime, enqueues Request\n126:   - `enqueueUpdate(old, new interface{})` - handles updates\n127:   - `enqueueDelete(obj interface{})` - handles deletions\n128:   - `enqueueOwnedPod(obj interface{})` - finds owner, enqueues AgentRuntime\n129:   - `enqueueOwnedPodUpdate(old, new interface{})`\n130:   - `enqueueOwnedPodDelete(obj interface{})`\n131: \n132: ### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterReconciler\n133: \n134: - [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `CodeInterpreterReconciler` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go`\n135:   - Fields: same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n136: \n137: - [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewCodeInterpreterReconciler()` constructor\n138:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n139:   - Registers event handlers on CodeInterpreter informer\n140: \n141: - [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement `Run()` method for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n142: \n143: - [ ] **TASK-033**: Implement `Reconcile()` method\n144:   - Same reconciliation pattern as AgentRuntimeReconciler\n145:   - Handles CodeInterpreter CRD\n146: \n147: - [ ] **TASK-034**: Implement `reconcileDeletion()` method for CodeInterpreter\n148: \n149: - [ ] **TASK-035**: Implement `reconcileSandboxPod()` method for CodeInterpreter\n150:   - Builds pod from CodeInterpreter spec\n151:   - Same create/update/delete pattern\n152: \n153: - [ ] **TASK-036**: Implement event handler methods for CodeInterpreterReconciler\n154: \n155: ### Phase 5: SandboxProcessor\n156: \n157: - [ ] **TASK-040**: Implement `SandboxProcessor` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sandbox_processor.go`\n158:   - Fields: `k8sClient`, `scheme`\n159: \n160: - [ ] **TASK-041**: Implement `NewSandboxProcessor()` constructor\n161: \n162: - [ ] **TASK-042**: Implement `BuildSandboxPod()` method for AgentRuntime\n163:   - Creates Pod with name `sandbox-{ar.Name}`\n164:   - Sets labels: `agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime`, `agentcube.volcano.sh/type`\n165:   - Builds PodSpec from AgentRuntime spec\n166:   - Sets owner reference\n167:   - Returns *corev1.Pod or error\n168: \n169: - [ ] **TASK-043**: Implement `buildPodSpec()` helper method\n170:   - Builds container spec from `ar.Spec.Container`\n171:   - Sets Resources, Ports, VolumeMounts\n172:   - Sets RestartPolicy=Never\n173:   - Sets SecurityContext, Affinity, Tolerations\n174:   - Adds code interpreter sidecar if enabled\n175: \n176: - [ ] **TASK-044**: Implement `BuildSandboxPod()` method for CodeInterpreter\n177:   - Similar to AgentRuntime but from CodeInterpreter spec\n178: \n179: - [ ] **TASK-045**: Implement `NeedsUpdate()` method\n180:   - Checks if container image changed\n181:   - Checks if resources changed\n182:   - Checks if environment variables changed\n183:   - Returns bool\n184: \n185: - [ ] **TASK-046**: Implement `UpdateSandboxPod()` method\n186:   - Deletes existing pod\n187:   - Waits for deletion (using wait.PollUntilContextTimeout)\n188:   - Creates new pod\n189:   - Returns *corev1.Pod or error\n190: \n191: - [ ] **TASK-047**: Implement helper functions\n192:   - `buildEnvFrom()` - converts env vars\n193:   - `buildResourceRequirements()` - converts resource quotas\n194:   - `buildContainerPorts()` - converts network spec\n195:   - `buildVolumeMounts()` and `buildVolumes()`\n196:   - `buildPodSecurityContext()`\n197:   - `buildAffinity()` and `buildTolerations()`\n198:   - `buildCodeInterpreterContainer()` - builds sidecar container\n199: \n200: ### Phase 6: StatusUpdater\n201: \n202: - [ ] **TASK-050**: Implement `StatusUpdater` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater.go`\n203:   - Field: `clientset`\n204: \n205: - [ ] **TASK-051**: Implement `NewStatusUpdater()` constructor\n206: \n207: - [ ] **TASK-052**: Implement `UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus()` method\n208:   - Creates deep copy of AgentRuntime\n209:   - Sets Phase based on pod state\n210:   - Sets SandboxRef\n211:   - Builds Conditions from pod\n212:   - Updates Endpoint if pod running\n213:   - Skips update if status unchanged\n214:   - Calls UpdateStatus subresource\n215: \n216: - [ ] **TASK-053**: Implement `UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus()` method\n217:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntime\n218: \n219: - [ ] **TASK-054**: Implement `mapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase()` function\n220:   - Maps PodPhase to AgentRuntimePhase/CodeInterpreterPhase\n221:   - Handles: Pending, Running, Failed, Succeeded, Unknown\n222: \n223: - [ ] **TASK-055**: Implement `buildConditionsFromPod()` function\n224:   - Converts PodConditions to CRD Conditions\n225: \n226: - [ ] **TASK-056**: Implement `buildEndpointFromPod()` function\n227:   - Builds endpoint URL from PodIP and container port\n228: \n229: ### Phase 7: OwnerReference Management\n230: \n231: - [ ] **TASK-060**: Implement `SetControllerReference()` function in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/owner_reference.go`\n232:   - Uses `metav1.NewControllerRef()`\n233:   - Sets owner reference on child object\n234: \n235: - [ ] **TASK-061**: Implement `IsOwnedBy()` function\n236:   - Checks if object has owner reference with matching UID and Controller=true\n237: \n238: - [ ] **TASK-062**: Implement `GetControllerOf()` helper\n239:   - Returns controller owner reference if exists\n240: \n241: ### Phase 8: Metrics\n242: \n243: - [ ] **TASK-070**: Implement `ReconcilerMetrics` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics.go`\n244:   - Fields: `reconcileDuration` (Histogram), `reconcileErrors` (Counter), `reconcileTotal` (Counter), `workqueueDepth` (Gauge), `workqueueLatency` (Histogram)\n245: \n246: - [ ] **TASK-071**: Implement `NewReconcilerMetrics()` constructor\n247:   - Creates Prometheus metrics with proper naming\n248:   - Registers metrics if registerer provided\n249: \n250: - [ ] **TASK-072**: Implement metric methods\n251:   - `observeReconcileDuration(d time.Duration)`\n252:   - `recordError(errorType string)`\n253:   - `recordReconcile()`\n254: \n255: ### Phase 9: Error Handling & Retry Logic\n256: \n257: - [ ] **TASK-080**: Implement centralized error handling in Reconcile methods\n258:   - Logs errors with context\n259:   - Records metrics\n260:   - Records events\n261:   - Determines retryability\n262: \n263: - [ ] **TASK-081**: Implement `calculateBackoff()` function\n264:   - Exponential backoff: baseDelay * 2^retryCount\n265:   - Max delay: 5 minutes\n266:   - Adds jitter (┬▒20%)\n267: \n268: - [ ] **TASK-082**: Handle k8s error types per design spec\n269:   - `IsNotFound` - skip reconciliation\n270:   - `IsAlreadyExists` - check if update needed\n271:   - `IsConflict` - re-fetch and retry\n272:   - `IsTimeout`, `IsTooManyRequests` - exponential backoff\n273: \n274: ### Phase 10: Configuration\n275: \n276: - [ ] **TASK-090**: Add reconciler flags in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n277:   - Flags: `--reconciler-resync-period`, `--reconciler-max-retries`, `--reconciler-rate-limit-qps`, `--reconciler-rate-limit-burst`, `--reconciler-concurrent`, `--reconciler-leader-election`, `--reconciler-leader-election-namespace`, `--reconciler-leader-election-name`\n278: \n279: - [ ] **TASK-091**: Integrate reconciler with main startup\n280:   - Load config\n281:   - Create ControllerManager\n282:   - Create reconcilers\n283:   - Add reconcilers to manager\n284:   - Start manager\n285: \n286: - [ ] **TASK-092**: Document environment variables\n287:   - `RECONCILER_RESYNC_PERIOD`, `RECONCILER_MAX_RETRIES`, `RECONCILER_RATE_LIMIT_QPS`, `RECONCILER_RATE_LIMIT_BURST`, `RECONCILER_CONCURRENT`, `RECONCILER_LEADER_ELECTION`, etc.\n288: \n289: ### Phase 11: Testing (TDD)\n290: \n291: #### Unit Tests - Reconciler\n292: \n293: - [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_Success` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler_test.go`\n294:   - Given: AgentRuntime in informer cache\n295:   - When: Reconcile() called\n296:   - Then: Pod created, no error, no requeue\n297:   - Use fake clientset + fake k8s client + mock informers\n298: \n299: - [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_PodExists`\n300:   - Given: AgentRuntime with existing owned pod\n301:   - When: Reconcile() called\n302:   - Then: No new pod created, status updated\n303: \n304: - [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_NeedsUpdate`\n305:   - Given: AgentRuntime with changed spec\n306:   - When: Reconcile() called\n307:   - Then: Pod deleted and recreated\n308: \n309: - [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_Deletion`\n310:   - Given: AgentRuntime with DeletionTimestamp set\n311:   - When: Reconcile() called\n312:   - Then: Pod deleted, finalizer removed\n313: \n314: - [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_NotFound`\n315:   - Given: Non-existent AgentRuntime\n316:   - When: Reconcile() called\n317:   - Then: No error, no requeue\n318: \n319: - [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_PodCreationFailed`\n320:   - Given: Invalid pod spec\n321:   - When: Reconcile() called\n322:   - Then: Error returned, event recorded, retry scheduled\n323: \n324: - [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestAgentRuntimeReconciler_Reconcile_StatusUpdateFailed`\n325:   - Given: Pod created but status update fails\n326:   - When: Reconcile() called\n327:   - Then: Error returned, event recorded, retry scheduled\n328: \n329: - [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Reconcile_Success`\n330:   - Same pattern as AgentRuntime tests\n331: \n332: - [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestCodeInterpreterReconciler_Reconcile_WithSidecar`\n333:   - Given: CodeInterpreter with code interpreter enabled\n334:   - When: Reconcile() called\n335:   - Then: Pod created with sidecar container\n336: \n337: #### Unit Tests - SandboxProcessor\n338: \n339: - [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestSandboxProcessor_BuildSandboxPod` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sandbox_processor_test.go`\n340:   - Given: AgentRuntime with full spec\n341:   - When: BuildSandboxPod() called\n342:   - Then: Pod has correct name, labels, owner reference, container spec\n343: \n344: - [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestSandboxProcessor_BuildSandboxPod_WithCodeInterpreter`\n345:   - Given: AgentRuntime with CodeInterpreter enabled\n346:   - When: BuildSandboxPod() called\n347:   - Then: Pod has sidecar container\n348: \n349: - [ ] **TEST-012**: `TestSandboxProcessor_NeedsUpdate_ImageChanged`\n350:   - Given: Pod with old image, AgentRuntime with new image\n351:   - When: NeedsUpdate() called\n352:   - Then: Returns true\n353: \n354: - [ ] **TEST-013**: `TestSandboxProcessor_NeedsUpdate_NoChange`\n355:   - Given: Pod matches AgentRuntime spec\n356:   - When: NeedsUpdate() called\n357:   - Then: Returns false\n358: \n359: - [ ] **TEST-014**: `TestSandboxProcessor_UpdateSandboxPod`\n360:   - Given: Pod needs update\n361:   - When: UpdateSandboxPod() called\n362:   - Then: Old pod deleted, new pod created\n363: \n364: #### Unit Tests - StatusUpdater\n365: \n366: - [ ] **TEST-015**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodRunning` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater_test.go`\n367:   - Given: AgentRuntime with running pod\n368:   - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n369:   - Then: Status.Phase=Running, SandboxRef set, Endpoint set\n370: \n371: - [ ] **TEST-016**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_PodPending`\n372:   - Given: AgentRuntime with pending pod\n373:   - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n374:   - Then: Status.Phase=Pending\n375: \n376: - [ ] **TEST-017**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus_NoChange`\n377:   - Given: Status unchanged\n378:   - When: UpdateAgentRuntimeStatus() called\n379:   - Then: No API call made\n380: \n381: - [ ] **TEST-018**: `TestStatusUpdater_UpdateCodeInterpreterStatus_PodRunning`\n382:   - Same pattern for CodeInterpreter\n383: \n384: #### Unit Tests - OwnerReference\n385: \n386: - [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestSetControllerReference` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/owner_reference_test.go`\n387:   - Given: Owner and child objects\n388:   - When: SetControllerReference() called\n389:   - Then: Child has owner reference with Controller=true\n390: \n391: - [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestIsOwnedBy_True`\n392:   - Given: Object with matching owner reference\n393:   - When: IsOwnedBy() called\n394:   - Then: Returns true\n395: \n396: - [ ] **TEST-022**: `TestIsOwnedBy_False`\n397:   - Given: Object with different owner\n398:   - When: IsOwnedBy() called\n399:   - Then: Returns false\n400: \n401: #### Unit Tests - Error Handling\n402: \n403: - [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestIsRetryableError_True` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors_test.go`\n404:   - Given: Timeout, TooManyRequests errors\n405:   - When: IsRetryableError() called\n406:   - Then: Returns true\n407: \n408: - [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestIsRetryableError_False`\n409:   - Given: NotFound, InvalidSpec errors\n410:   - When: IsRetryableError() called\n411:   - Then: Returns false\n412: \n413: - [ ] **TEST-032**: `TestCalculateBackoff`\n414:   - Given: Various retry counts\n415:   - When: calculateBackoff() called\n416:   - Then: Returns exponentially increasing delays with jitter\n417: \n418: #### Unit Tests - Metrics\n419: \n420: - [ ] **TEST-040**: `TestReconcilerMetrics_ObserveReconcileDuration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/metrics_test.go`\n421:   - Given: Metrics registered\n422:   - When: observeReconcileDuration() called\n423:   - Then: Histogram updated\n424: \n425: - [ ] **TEST-041**: `TestReconcilerMetrics_RecordError`\n426:   - Given: Metrics registered\n427:   - When: recordError() called\n428:   - Then: Counter incremented\n429: \n430: 