[ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/doc.go`\n481:   - Package overview\n482:   - Architecture description\n483:   - Usage example\n484: \n485: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n486:   - Document parameters, return values\n487:   - Document error conditions\n488:   - Include examples where applicable\n489: \n490: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Document reconciliation loop in code comments\n491:   - Step-by-step flow\n492:   - Error handling strategy\n493:   - Retry behavior\n494: \n495: - [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md`\n496:   - Add reconciler architecture section\n497:   - Include component diagram\n498:   - Document configuration options\n499:   - List environment variables\n500: \n501: - [ ] **DOC-005**: Add API contracts documentation\n502:   - Reconciliation contract\n503:   - Owner reference pattern\n504:   - Status update contract\n505:   - Event recording\n506: \n507: ## Acceptance Criteria\n508: \n509: - [ ] ControllerManager implemented with proper lifecycle management\n510: - [ ] AgentRuntimeReconciler implemented with full reconciliation loop\n511: - [ ] CodeInterpreterReconciler implemented with full reconciliation loop\n512: - [ ] SandboxProcessor builds pods from both CRD types\n513: - [ ] StatusUpdater updates CRD status based on pod state\n514: - [ ] Owner reference management ensures proper garbage collection\n515: - [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n516: - [ ] Error handling covers all spec-defined scenarios\n517: - [ ] Retry logic with exponential backoff implemented\n518: - [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n519: - [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n520: - [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented and tested\n521: - [ ] Integration with client-go informers and listers verified\n522: - [ ] Workqueue rate limiting functional\n523: - [ ] Events recorded for significant reconciliation actions\n524: - [ ] Configuration via flags and environment variables\n525: - [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n526: \n527: ## Dependencies\n528: \n529: - **Completed**: ST-1 (CRD schemas), ST-2 (client-go typed clients, informers, listers)\n530: - **Required**: CRDs (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) registered and served\n531: - **Required**: RBAC permissions for watching CRDs and managing Pods\n532: - **Required**: SharedInformerFactory operational\n533: - **Related**: AR-004 (HTTP server) - reconciler runs alongside HTTP server\n\n(End of file - total 533 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 ŌĆö K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ© Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-007 ŌĆö K8s Reconciler µÄ¦ÕłČÕÖ© |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | L |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Data Structures & Types\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `Reconciler` interface in `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n  - Methods: `Run(ctx context.Context)`, `Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req Request) (Result, error)`\n  - Document each method purpose\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-007/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775846612967,"end":1775846612989}}}}
