{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846678280,"sessionID":"ses_2874b5d29ffeeDhVXE2ZEQcEQq","part":{"id":"prt_d78b50292001hUNPIVEYEj4VG3","messageID":"msg_d78b4f2b2001R1dsx0sciVeLrH","sessionID":"ses_2874b5d29ffeeDhVXE2ZEQcEQq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1a5eb18c8043487ea8995116","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/README.md","content":"# AR-008 ŌĆö Sandbox GC Õ«ÜµŚČµĖģńÉåµ£║ÕłČ\n\n**Module:** pkg/workloadmanager  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement sandbox garbage collection mechanism for periodic cleanup of idle/orphaned sandboxes in the pkg/workloadmanager module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Design GC strategy and policies\n- [ ] Implement GC core logic\n- [ ] Add cleanup scheduling\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n- [ ] Add integration tests\n\n## Notes\n\nSee `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n\n## Source Files\n\nSee `src/` directory for source code changes.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/README.md","time":{"start":1775846678260,"end":1775846678279}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846678282,"sessionID":"ses_2874b5d29ffeeDhVXE2ZEQcEQq","part":{"id":"prt_d78b512aa001B7slcffctKdpv6","messageID":"msg_d78b4f2b2001R1dsx0sciVeLrH","sessionID":"ses_2874b5d29ffeeDhVXE2ZEQcEQq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2123352db69a418f89747578","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","content":"# AR-008 ŌĆö Sandbox GC Õ«ÜµŚČµĖģńÉåµ£║ÕłČ Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 ŌĆö Sandbox GC Õ«ÜµŚČµĖģńÉåµ£║ÕłČ |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: GC Policy & Configuration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Define `GCConfig` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/config.go`\n  - Fields: `Enabled` (bool), `Interval` (time.Duration), `IdleTimeout` (time.Duration), `MaxIdleCount` (int), `DryRun` (bool)\n  - Document each field with comments\n\n- [ ] **TASK-002**: Implement `DefaultGCConfig()` function\n  - Returns default configuration: Enabled=true, Interval=5m, IdleTimeout=30m, MaxIdleCount=100, DryRun=false\n\n- [ ] **TASK-003**: Define `SandboxState` enum/consts in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/state.go`\n  - States: `StateActive`, `StateIdle`, `StateOrphaned`, `StateExpired`\n  - Document state transition rules\n\n- [ ] **TASK-004**: Define `GCCandidate` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/candidate.go`\n  - Fields: `Name`, `Namespace`, `State`, `LastActivity` (time.Time), `CreatedAt` (time.Time), `OwnerRef` (string)\n  - Methods: `IsExpired()`, `IsIdle()`\n\n### Phase 2: GC Core Logic\n\n- [ ] **TASK-010**: Implement `GarbageCollector` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc.go`\n  - Fields: `config`, `clientset`, `workloadManager`, `ctx`, `cancel`, `ticker`, `metrics`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-011**: Implement `NewGarbageCollector()` constructor\n  - Takes config, clientset, workloadManager\n  - Returns initialized *GarbageCollector\n\n- [ ] **TASK-012**: Implement `Start()` method\n  - Creates context\n  - Starts ticker with configured interval\n  - Runs initial GC scan\n  - Blocks until ctx.Done()\n\n- [ ] **TASK-013**: Implement `Stop()` method\n  - Cancels context\n  - Stops ticker\n  - Logs shutdown\n\n- [ ] **TASK-014**: Implement `runGC()` method\n  - Scans all sandboxes\n  - Evaluates each against GC policy\n  - Collects candidates for cleanup\n  - Executes cleanup\n  - Records metrics\n\n- [ ] **TASK-015**: Implement `scanSandboxes()` method\n  - Lists all AgentRuntime sandboxes\n  - Lists all CodeInterpreter sandboxes\n  - Evaluates state for each\n  - Returns list of GCCandidate\n\n- [ ] **TASK-016**: Implement `evaluateState()` method\n  - Checks last activity timestamp\n  - Checks owner existence\n  - Determines sandbox state (Active/Idle/Orphaned/Expired)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-017**: Implement `cleanup()` method\n  - Filters candidates by state\n  - Respects MaxIdleCount (keeps most recent)\n  - Deletes expired/orphaned sandboxes\n  - Deletes excess idle sandboxes\n  - Returns cleanup summary\n\n### Phase 3: Activity Tracking\n\n- [ ] **TASK-020**: Implement `LastActivityTracker` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/activity.go`\n  - Tracks last activity timestamp per sandbox\n  - Fields: `mu` (sync.RWMutex), `activities` (map[string]time.Time)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-021**: Implement `RecordActivity()` method\n  - Updates last activity timestamp for sandbox\n\n- [ ] **TASK-022**: Implement `GetLastActivity()` method\n  - Returns last activity timestamp or zero time\n\n- [ ] **TASK-023**: Implement `GetIntegrations()` for activity sources\n  - HTTP request middleware integration point\n  - Session creation/deletion hooks\n\n### Phase 4: Metrics\n\n- [ ] **TASK-030**: Implement `GCMetrics` struct in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics.go`\n  - Fields: `gcRuns` (Counter), `gcDuration` (Histogram), `sandboxesScanned` (Gauge), `sandboxesCleaned` (Counter), `sandboxesByState` (GaugeVec)\n\n- [ ] **TASK-031**: Implement `NewGCMetrics()` constructor\n  - Creates Prometheus metrics\n  - Registers with registerer\n\n- [ ] **TASK-032**: Implement metric methods\n  - `recordRun(duration time.Duration)`\n  - `recordScanned(count int)`\n  - `recordCleaned(count int)`\n  - `updateStateCounts(stateCounts map[SandboxState]int)`\n\n### Phase 5: Configuration Integration\n\n- [ ] **TASK-040**: Add GC flags in `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n  - Flags: `--gc-enabled`, `--gc-interval`, `--gc-idle-timeout`, `--gc-max-idle-count`, `--gc-dry-run`\n\n- [ ] **TASK-041**: Integrate GC with main startup\n  - Load config\n  - Create GarbageCollector\n  - Start GC as goroutine\n  - Register shutdown hook\n\n- [ ] **TASK-042**: Document environment variables\n  - `GC_ENABLED`, `GC_INTERVAL`, `GC_IDLE_TIMEOUT`, `GC_MAX_IDLE_COUNT`, `GC_DRY_RUN`\n\n### Phase 6: Testing (TDD)\n\n#### Unit Tests - GC Core\n\n- [ ] **TEST-001**: `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc_test.go`\n  - Given: Configured GC\n  - When: Start() then Stop() called\n  - Then: GC runs without error, graceful shutdown\n\n- [ ] **TEST-002**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_ExpiredSandboxes`\n  - Given: Sandboxes exceeding idle timeout\n  - When: runGC() called\n  - Then: Expired sandboxes deleted, metrics recorded\n\n- [ ] **TEST-003**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_OrphanedSandboxes`\n  - Given: Sandboxes without valid owner\n  - When: runGC() called\n  - Then: Orphaned sandboxes deleted\n\n- [ ] **TEST-004**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_MaxIdleCount`\n  - Given: More idle sandboxes than MaxIdleCount\n  - When: runGC() called\n  - Then: Oldest idle sandboxes deleted, keeps most recent\n\n- [ ] **TEST-005**: `TestGarbageCollector_runGC_DryRun`\n  - Given: DryRun=true, expired sandboxes exist\n  - When: runGC() called\n  - Then: No sandboxes deleted, metrics show what would be cleaned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-006**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Active`\n  - Given: Sandbox with recent activity\n  - When: evaluateState() called\n  - Then: Returns StateActive\n\n- [ ] **TEST-007**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Idle`\n  - Given: Sandbox with no recent activity but within timeout\n  - When: evaluateState() called\n  - Then: Returns StateIdle\n\n- [ ] **TEST-008**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Expired`\n  - Given: Sandbox exceeding idle timeout\n  - When: evaluateState() called\n  - Then: Returns StateExpired\n\n- [ ] **TEST-009**: `TestGarbageCollector_evaluateState_Orphaned`\n  - Given: Sandbox with missing owner\n  - When: evaluateState() called\n  - Then: Returns StateOrphaned\n\n#### Unit Tests - Activity Tracker\n\n- [ ] **TEST-010**: `TestLastActivityTracker_RecordAndGet` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/activity_test.go`\n  - Given: New tracker\n  - When: RecordActivity() then GetLastActivity()\n  - Then: Returns recorded timestamp\n\n- [ ] **TEST-011**: `TestLastActivityTracker_GetLastActivity_NotFound`\n  - Given: New tracker, no activity recorded\n  - When: GetLastActivity() called\n  - Then: Returns zero time\n\n#### Unit Tests - GC Candidate\n\n- [ ] **TEST-020**: `TestGCCandidate_IsExpired` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/candidate_test.go`\n  - Given: Candidate with LastActivity exceeding timeout\n  - When: IsExpired() called\n  - Then: Returns true\n\n- [ ] **TEST-021**: `TestGCCandidate_IsIdle`\n  - Given: Candidate with no recent activity\n  - When: IsIdle() called\n  - Then: Returns true\n\n#### Unit Tests - Metrics\n\n- [ ] **TEST-030**: `TestGCMetrics_RecordRun` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/metrics_test.go`\n  - Given: Metrics registered\n  - When: recordRun() called\n  - Then: Counter and histogram updated\n\n- [ ] **TEST-031**: `TestGCMetrics_RecordCleaned`\n  - Given: Metrics registered\n  - When: recordCleaned() called\n  - Then: Counter incremented\n\n#### Test Infrastructure\n\n- [ ] **TEST-040**: Create `newTestGC()` helper in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/gc_test.go`\n  - Creates fake clientset, config, mock workloadManager\n  - Returns initialized GC for testing\n\n- [ ] **TEST-041**: Create test fixtures\n  - `buildAgentRuntime()` - creates test AgentRuntime objects\n  - `buildCodeInterpreter()` - creates test CodeInterpreter objects\n  - `buildSandboxWithActivity()` - creates sandboxes with specific activity timestamps\n\n#### Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] **TEST-050**: `TestGarbageCollector_Integration` in `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/integration_test.go`\n  - Use envtest or real K8s cluster\n  - Create sandboxes with various states\n  - Run GC\n  - Verify correct sandboxes cleaned\n\n- [ ] **TEST-051**: `TestGarbageCollector_PeriodicRun`\n  - Start GC with short interval\n  - Verify GC runs periodically\n  - Verify metrics accumulated\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation\n\n- [ ] **DOC-001**: Add package documentation to `pkg/workloadmanager/gc/doc.go`\n  - Package overview\n  - GC strategy description\n  - Configuration options\n\n- [ ] **DOC-002**: Add godoc comments to all public types and functions\n\n- [ ] **DOC-003**: Document GC policy decision logic in code comments\n  - State evaluation rules\n  - Cleanup priority order\n\n- [ ] **DOC-004**: Update `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md`\n  - Add GC section\n  - Document configuration options\n  - List environment variables\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] GC runs periodically at configured interval\n- [ ] Expired sandboxes (exceeding idle timeout) are cleaned\n- [ ] Orphaned sandboxes (missing owner) are cleaned\n- [ ] MaxIdleCount limit enforced (oldest idle sandboxes removed)\n- [ ] DryRun mode logs without deleting\n- [ ] Activity tracking integrated with HTTP middleware\n- [ ] Metrics exported for Prometheus\n- [ ] All tests pass (unit + integration)\n- [ ] Test coverage ratio > 0.5\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown implemented\n- [ ] Configuration via flags and environment variables\n- [ ] Godoc documentation complete\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- **Required**: pkg/workloadmanager base module\n- **Required**: Access to K8s clientset for listing/deleting sandboxes\n- **Related**: AR-007 (K8s Reconciler) - GC coordinates with reconciler state\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-008/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775846678267,"end":1775846678281}}}}
